HEADWORD: Superordination
<hw>Su`per*or`di*na"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Pref. <ets>super-</ets> + <ets>ordination</ets>: cf. L. <ets>superordinatio</ets>.]</ety> <def>The ordination of a person to fill a station already occupied; especially, the ordination by an ecclesiastical official, during his lifetime, of his successor.</def>  <rj><au>Fuller.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

